Full Title: 4th International Conference on Intercultural Pragmatics=20

Date: 15-Nov-2010 - 17-Nov-2010
Location: Madrid, Spain=20
Contact Person: Jes=FAs Romero-Trillo
Meeting Email: jesus.romero@uam.es
Web Site: http://www.clancorpus.net=20

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Pragmatics; Sociolinguistics=20

Call Deadline: 15-Mar-2010=20

Meeting Description:

The goal of the conference is to promote both theoretical and applied resea=
rch
in pragmatics.=20

Call for Papers

Abstracts are invited for papers on any topic relevant to the fields of
pragmatics and intercultural communication. Three parallel sessions will be=
 held:

- Pragmatics theories: meaning, role of context, semantics-pragmatics=20
interface, explicature, implicature, speech act theory, etc.
- Intercultural aspects of pragmatics: research involving more than one=20
language and culture or varieties of one language, lingua franca,=20
intercultural misunderstandings, effect of dual language and multilingual=
=20
systems on the development and use of pragmatic skills
- Applications: usage and corpus-based approaches, teachability and=20
learnability of pragmatic skills, pragmatic variations within one language =
and=20
across languages, developmental pragmatics, etc.

Please send an abstract (max. 300 words) to the two addresses below before =
15th
March 2010.

madrid@clancorpus.net
jesus.romero@uam.es

Please, include your name, affiliation and e-mail address. Abstracts will b=
e
double-blind peer-reviewed, and should include sufficient detail to allow
reviewers to judge the scientific merits of the work. Paper presentations w=
ill
be allowed 20 minutes, plus 10 minutes for questions.

